column3: Ealdwine, treasure hunter extraordinaire, appears somewhat out of sorts.

Through slurred speech, Ealdwine kindly offers to give you his last mysterious map, before remembering that he isn't at liberty to do so; instead, he bids you deliver it to his mother at Revenant's Toll. See the map safely to Brangwine, lest poor Ealdwine be on the receiving end of a bloody flogging.

Brangwine informs you that mysterious maps work like a charm on kitchen stains, and expresses her willingness to part with some from her stores. To be king of your kitchen, you must bring her the object of her morbid desires.
Deliver the map to Brangwine at Revenant's Toll.

Why, hello there, young one. What can old Brangwine do for you, hmmm?

Oh my, a mysterious map! My drunken lout of a son has you running errands, I see. For that, I apologize. Rest assured he will be suitably \x02\x1a\x02\x02\x03disciplined\x02\x1a\x02\x01\x03 for his indiscretion.
Why do I collect these maps, you ask? Well, it just so happens they remove kitchen stains like a charm. Something to do with the special ink they bear, I believe.
If you want your kitchen to be spotless like mine, I wouldn't be averse to parting with a map or three. My son keeps my stores constantly replenished, you see.

In exchange, I ask that you bring me...oh, let us say, articles found upon adventurers who \x02\x1a\x02\x02\x03mis\x02\x1a\x02\x01\x03adventured. The gods know they have no further need of their worldly possessions, so you need not feel guilty.
Where are these articles like to be found? Why, where the deadliest creatures prowl, of course. Adventurers are drawn to them like moths to a flame, are they not?

By your questioning look, I take it you're wondering what interest I have in such \x02\x1a\x02\x02\x03salvaged\x02\x1a\x02\x01\x03 items. You have secrets that you would sooner take to the grave, do you not? Let me keep mine, young one, and I will let you keep yours.
A repeatable quest is now available from Brangwine at Revenant's Toll.
Completing the quest will earn you a mysterious map.
